Content Project Coordinator		CrowdSource		Greater St. Louis Area		<div class="rich-text" itemprop="description"><p>Are you passionate about quality web content? Does the idea of managing large-scale online content projects with thousands of freelance writers for some of the world’s biggest companies get you pumped? Yes? Keep reading. We’re CrowdSource, the industry leader in the multi-billion dollar crowdsourcing market, providing clients with on-demand access to a network of freelancers to solve their web content problems. </p><p></p><p>We’re a team of incredibly smart and dedicated people—all working toward the same goal: to be the best in the world at helping enterprise clients leverage the world of freelance talent. <strong>And our people come first</strong><strong>.</strong> </p><p></p><p>At CrowdSource, our Project Coordinators work with key stakeholders to design and build project plans that help clients execute their strategic content objectives. The role is very hands-on, working with internal teams as well as managing the freelancers completing various content projects. You’ll be joining 4 other Project Coordinators on the Content side of the Client Operations Team, reporting to our VP of Client Services, Jayme O’Renic. </p><p>  </p><p><strong>In this role, you will:</strong> </p><ul><li>Work with Account Managers to understand client needs </li></ul><ul><li>Write project instructions for freelancers that are clear and concise </li></ul><ul><li>Design and create project plans within our proprietary software </li></ul><ul><li>Identify areas for improvement on projects and proposing appropriate solutions </li></ul><ul><li>Review and approve all project deliverables to ensure quality standards and project expectations are met </li></ul><ul><li>Implement proper screening methods (tests, samples, surveys, etc.) to ensure the right freelancers have access to the right projects </li></ul><ul><li>Coach freelancers’ performance throughout the lifecycle of a project via email and forums; including resolving disputes, communicating instruction changes, and providing constructive performance feedback </li></ul><ul><li>Within defined parameters, develop incentives for freelancers, motivating them to improve turnaround time and increase productivity </li></ul><ul><li>Absorb freelancer feedback and prioritize its importance; responding and making updates to project to mitigate concerns </li></ul><ul><li>Manage multiple projects at once, keeping track of all deadlines, deliverables, and associated tasks </li></ul><ul><li>Collaborate with the project team to determine internal costs and scope of project plans </li></ul><ul><li>Ensure that project issues are dealt with in an efficient manner, informing the project team of any problems that may arise </li></ul><ul><li>Provide regular input on all project activity, including weekly status updates </li></ul><ul><li>Complete other duties as assigned </li></ul><p> </p></div><div class="rich-text" itemprop="description"><p>CrowdSource offers managed crowdsourcing solutions to meet businesses’ most intense content and large-scale data needs with quality, speed and scale. <br /> <br />We are experts in creating specialized content for marketers, retailers, agencies and publishers. By leveraging a crowd of experienced writers and editors, we produce quality content at scale. Before projects begin, we test our workforce and evaluate individual capabilities. Our in-house experts manage our workforce teams, in addition to the several layers of quality controls built into our system, ensuring accuracy, validity and quality of each task completed. In return, our clients receive the highest-quality content both quickly and efficiently. <br /> <br />Follow us on social media: <br /> Twitter - https://twitter.com/crowdsource <br /> Facebook - https://www.facebook.com/CrowdSourcecom <br /> Google+ - google.com/+Crowdsource <br /> Instagram - https://instagram.com/crowdsource/ <br /> CrowdSource Blog - 